{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the contribution of our research is as follows: (i) we comprehensively explore the reason for explainable social media recommendation from end users' perspective, (ii) empirically investigate the required explanation attributes for designing and developing an explainable social media recommendation platform, (iii) proposed a framework that shows how an explainable social media recommendation can impact users social media experience, (iv) developed a synthesized framework based on the concepts of design science research (Hevner et al., 2004; Peffers et al., 2007), which helps the practitioners to develop an explainable recommendation system, (v) identified the implications of affordance in explainable social media recommendation platforms (Bucher & Helmond, 2018; Leonardi, 2011), and (vi) our findings can address the policy guidelines of HLEG, the AI Act, and GDPR to some extent (Durovic & Corno, 2025).",
    "The rest of the paper is organized as follows: the next section outlines the background to the study, which gives a summary of critical issues in social media recommendation, the basics of an explainable recommendation system, and related works; the following section describes the research strategy and research methodology used in this work, the study area and study design, the data analysis and reporting process, and the validity and reliability checking process; the next section discusses the findings based on our interview data which outlines the mapping demographic information and thematic analysis with the research questions under consideration; after that, this research proposes design recommendations and a synthesized framework for explainable recommendation interface design; after that, the paper discusses the theoretical and practical implications of our research; the next section discusses the limitations and future research directions of the study; and finally, the paper concludes with a summary of findings and recommendations.",
    "Explainable recommendation research has gained its pace since Zhang et al. (2014) coined the term \"explainable recommendation\" in their work followed by the seminal work of Gunning et al. (2019).",
    "Recommendation systems use algorithms to predict and deliver specific suggestions (Barile et al., 2024).",
    "Generally, recommendation systems can be divided into two types: personalized and non-personalized recommendation systems."
  ],
